 but with maybe 50-100 toons on my screen lag was pretty bad.<br>
 someone told me last night but it was late and i forget. what is the command to turn spell effects off? and does turning names off really help?<br>
 anyone that says Hibernia is broken is wrong. when we come together we are a force to be dealt with :)<br>
 ~ mugs ~ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utandaina.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tandaina</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(1/4/02 9:04:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: my first real rvr</span><hr size=1> I agree, Hib ain't broken. Just takes more finesse to play eh? ;)<br>
<br>
I was in my first big fight last night too.  (You on Bev Mug?) Wasn't nearly as laggy as I thought it'd be.  But I play with names off, maybe that helps.  (In that mess names don't do a hill of beans anyway.  I just clicked on the shiney plate helms to target enemies. ;)<br>
<br>
I didn't know you could turn off spell effects in DAoC.  Hmm... I'm not sure I'd WANT to, too important to be able to see the casters and what spells they're casting.<br>
<br>
/runs like heck from the giant fire ball flying toward her. <p>Silverleaf Goldenthorn<BR>
Warden of Connla
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umalbor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Malbor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Druid in Absentia<br>Moderator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(1/4/02 12:20:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/malbor/malbor.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: my first real rvr</span><hr size=1> <br>
FYI<br>
<br>
When people speak of turning off spell effects, they are referring to renaming the folder that contains the files that display the affects AFTER you're past the patching process.  I don't recall the folder name. <br>
<br>
There may also be another way, but this is the only way I'm aware of.<br>
<br>
