</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unyssarainwhisper.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nyssa Rainwhisper</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://arnemetia.homestead.com/files/MiscImages/bluepawbullet.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(1/4/02 10:38:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://arnemetia.homestead.com/files/MiscImages/zidane.gif WIDTH=64 HEIGHT=64></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: my first real rvr</span><hr size=1> Now please keep in mind that I don't want to turn this into a Hibernia is/isn't broken rant, but I just want to bring forth some issues I've experienced with Hibernia.  Hibernia, imo has been a bit neglected.<br>
<br>
While a huge amount of people bonding together to form a force is strong, as a Hibernian I still think we are under balanced compared to the likes of Midgard.  For example.  I was hunting in Cruachan Gorge several days ago with a group of 7 people ranging from 28th lvl to 35, when one single Midgard healer (rumored to be 45th lvl) came by, AE mezzed my group, stunned each of us one by one, and took her sweet time clubbing us to death.  It took at least 2 groups several of which were post 40th to chase that runt down and beat her senseless.  Um...I call that an imbalance wouldn't you?<br>
<br>
Also, bards in Hibernia (as well as Albion) have obnoxious fancy glowing neon green notes merrily floating around them when they sing.  What do skalds have in Midgard?  All shouts, no notes, no way of indicating they are one of the primary targets in RvR due to their abilities.<br>
<br>
Other things such as spell effect eye candy.  Albion casters get a fancy schmancy gemlike effect when they buff.  What do we get?  A big round blue ball.  Albion casters also have cool looking fireball-like eexplosions for fire spells.  What do our Eldritches get for spell effects?  A black blast that looks like a land mine went off sending dirt in the air.  Whoopie.  Midgard Thanes have lightening bolts that actually looks like lightening bolts.  What do our Champions get?  A whole lotta nothing.<br>
<br>
We can't even get drops in our dungeons that aids our tradeskills like Midgard does.<br>
<br>
I don't mean to be negative, I really still enjoy playing in Hibernia, but face it, we lack some pretty basic things.<br>
<br>
Congrats on your first RvR battle, Mugs.  It's exhilirating and fun isn't it?  There's nothing more satisfying than slaughtering an enemy and seeing that you got some realm points from them. :) <p><CENTER>
