<font size=1 color=red>Meridian 59 lives!</a> - Salicia of 102</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umacnat.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Macnat</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://hem1.passagen.se/lonnelid/english.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(1/7/02 6:56:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: my first real rvr</span><hr size=1> definatly a lvl issue, but a lvl 45 Warrior cant solo a lvl 1 in RvR let alone an entire group of greys ... unless they are dumb enough not to run. <p><A HREF="http://www.e-panaphobia.com/daoc/"><IMG SRC="http://homepage.ntlworld.com/nigel_b/kibuka.jpg">
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udragoon412.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dragoon412</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(1/7/02 9:11:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: my first real rvr</span><hr size=1> Macnat, a warrior could easily take out a small group of greys 10-17 levels below him. Aside from the fact that the greys would be lucky to land a hit or spell on him, warriors are like damage sponges. I can't tell you how many times I've sat there with my healer in some tank-heavy group with a warrior up front thinking that it's just not right for them to take so much abuse and keep fighting. <p>--For every winner, there are dozens of losers. Odds are you're one of 'em. 
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unyssarainwhisper.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nyssa Rainwhisper</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://arnemetia.homestead.com/files/MiscImages/bluepawbullet.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(1/7/02 12:06:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://arnemetia.homestead.com/files/MiscImages/zidane.gif WIDTH=64 HEIGHT=64></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: my first real rvr</span><hr size=1> Sure lvl makes a difference in DAoC.  Doesn't it always make a difference regardless of what MMORPG you play?  My point was, Healers in Midgard are, imo a bit too powerful because they are essentially a druid and bard rolled into one.  They can heal, buff (including run speed), <i>and</i> mez/stun.  That's like having a cleric/enchanter/druid cross in EQ terms.  That makes them very dangerous in RvR.  But before you think I'm whining about how my realm sucks, nerf healers, I play a healer in Midgard too.  Sure Hibernian bards can heal, buff (somewhat), and mez, but they cannot AE mez a group, go up and stun each one of them and club you to death.  They can't even wear plate-type armors like a Healer can.<br>
<br>
It's pretty obvious Hibernia is lacking in many areas since Mythic themselves admitted that they spent the least amount of time developing the realm.  Honestly now, what does an onion shaped, Taj Mahal looking like palace have anything to do with Celtic mythology?  If Hibernia wasn't lacking, there wouldn't be so many people fleeing to make characters in Albion or Midgard and there wouldn't be posts entitled "<A HREF="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showMessage?topicID=241.topic">So is Hibernia dying?</A>"<br>
<br>
I don't think that Hibernia completely sucks, but we sure could use some work. <p><CENTER>
